A Saudi Arabian court sentenced a
former mayor of Jeddah to five years in prison and fined him
100,000 riyals ($27,000) for accepting bribes, failing to
perform his duties and wasting public money,  Arab News  reported,
citing the court decision.  The defendant said he disagreed with the verdict, the
